Then get your definitions straight first off. If you wanna argue AC reduces damage taken, fine. If we're going down that path, then let's talk about the soft cap. Granted, it's higher since PoP, but that doesn't change the fact that AC figures produce severely diminishing returns past the 1200ish mark.<br>
<br>
[qupte]&quot;Wrong. Increasing attack increases your max hit up to a threshold that is dependent on class and level. Find a level 60 warrior with 1000 atk and parse long enough to find his max hit. Now give him enough STR buffs/gear and +atk buffs/gear to raise his atk considerably and then find his max hit. At level 60 it will top out at 5.7 times weapon damage plus damage bonus...but not until he has reached a certain atk threshold. 1000 atk is well below that threshold.&quot;[/quote]<br>
<br>
Two things. 1, level 60 warriors don't have 1000atk. They have significantly more than that if they have their lvl 60 skills. Take a lvl 60 warrior, parse him, see his max hit. Give him avatar, or CoP, his max hit remains the same. His damage increases, but max remains. I've parsed myself, at 60 and 65. At both lvls, my max hit duel-wielding did not change with addition of any +str or +atk buffs, but how many times I attained it did.<br>
<br>
