<br>
Watch what people do in your group and react to it. If a mob reaches the camp and you see your enchanter starting to cast a spell, then you should know that tash or slow is about to hit the mob. Be ready for it, as soon as you see that spell text on the mob you should hit your taunt key. Hell there is NO reason not to shield your enchanter or slower as soon as the fight starts. /shield has such a fast refresh time that it's almost always ready before the next pull, in most elemental exp groups I'm in.<br>
<br>
If you are breaking a mez and you have /shield up, then use it. It's always a good thing to play it safe, and the best part is people will comment positively about you. People will come to expect having a tank who shields them all the time, and they will keep asking you to their groups.<br>
<br>
If you're having problems holding aggression then ask you enchanter to cast their aggression buff on you. I'm sure they would be more then happy to do it, and it cost a low amount of mana to be any kind of factor on mana usage. <br>
<br>
Try to seach for a high end 2 hander when trying to tank in PoP. I parsed 150 DPS (average) last night in a plane of water group using my Blade of War. That is 5 less DPS then the rogue in our group was doing. I'm not sure about you, but when I'm showing up rogues and tanking quad 1k hitting mobs fine, I start to feel really good about my class.  <p><a href= http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=110313 target="_blank">Just another dead tank</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=karthunk>Karthunk</A> at: 3/5/03 4:26:23 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luthair>Luthair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/03 9:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: nuker's agro</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Pally's don't have to chain stun every mob that comes in, they will do more damage if they just melee the darn thing, but for some reason unknown to me they feel the need to chain stun for a few rounds of combat to get it on them, then they laugh about it in group chat. I have seen people like this and they are on my no group list<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
