</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=frodlin7th>Frodlin7th</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 329<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/03 3:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: nuker's agro</span><hr size=1> Take a long, hard look at the data found on that cleric thread with regards to mitigation.  It's a real eye opener, particularly when Clerics have a much lower 'defense&quot; skill than warriors.   It's entirely possible that the 'defense&quot; skill *only* relates to the AC number, and has no bearing whatsoever on mitigation.<br>
<br>
Just for those who don't want to pore through the thread... in a nutshell this is it:<br>
<br>
Clerics were concerned because they die fast on raids and stuff.   They thought that they were being ripped off in terms of being considered to have &quot;plate mitigation&quot;.  A similar discussion ensued as to what constituted &quot;mitigation&quot;, and someone ran some tests in HoH, with a cleric and warrior with the same AC and Agi.   it turned out that the *only* substantive difference between the two classes had nothing to do with Mitigation at all, mitigation was almost identical, it was in avoidance, and the obvious hitpoint pool advantage of a warrior which made them more &quot;tankable&quot; than clerics.<br>
<br>
