<br>
Frod, the defense skill plays a very small part in mitigation. Mitigation is almost completely made up of raw item AC. Defense plays a very major role in avoidance.<br>
<br>
EDIT: something I wanted to point out in regard to that cleric parse. The cleric and the warrior had essentially identical AC and AGI for the test. The warrior has 108 more avoidance AC than the cleric does. That means that for their total AC to be equal, the cleric has 108 more mitigation AC than the warrior does...and still mitigates worse than the warrior does. The cleric's average hit was 9.7 DI and the warrior's average was 9.2 DI. His cleric obviously has alot more raw item AC than his warrior does, 68 or 69 raw item AC. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686">Graal MacBladefury</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
