Killing things fast and furious results in out of whack aggro, saying people should not overaggro and let the warrior build hate is like telling them to exp slower.<br>
<br>
So they pick SKs or PAL tanks, much less aggro problems. The mobs die fast and exp is flowing.<br>
<br>
Get the picture ? It wont help complaining that others slow or nuke etc they want exp fast and steady and not &quot;careful godforbid I overaggro&quot; fights that take twice as long with a war than a pal / sk.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I'd like to say thats how I feel like &quot;in the trenches&quot; of POV/POS as they say...<br>
<br>
Now before I get everybody's knickers in a twist (and blacklist myself), its not really a class thing. You get a tremendous amount of leeway in an exp group when you have ANYONE (rather than ANY CLASS) that can <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>generate and maintain aggro</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> at will. I have seen warriors sucking the aggro of mobs to them like a magnet and I have seen warriors just plain suck <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    . THE SAME applies to hybrids I must say.... Once you have the luxury of stacking debuffs on the mobs FAST without worry, the kill rate goes up significantly and the exp flows like water.<br>
<br>
We are arguing the technicalities and numbers of the warrior taunt and their tanking ability. That a warrior is the best meatshield tank there is; is without argument. Rather what I think is a more productive line of thinking and discussion is what sort of skills and equipment that a warrior needs to learn or acquire that will put them in a competitive footing with similarly equipped heavy plate hybrids.<br>
<br>
PS: <br>
A lot of the discussion above about damage mitigation is moot. Once you are able slap on a 75% shaman slow (or a 70% enchanter slow), even a Monk, Ranger or a Rogue can tank down a POV mob (fungal fiend is my personal example) IF the healer isn't blind, dead or AFK. Its a matter of just how efficient it is for the group to do so - healer mana used up per kill.<br>
<br>
IMHO, from my own anecdotal experience - on slowed mobs (second tier POP mobs) - there is NO practical difference in between having a warrior or a heavy plate hybrid (SK/Pally) as the MT - GIVEN that the warrs and hybrids have level appropriate armor and skills. If there is a theoretical difference, I see non in practice. <p><hr />
